From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 06:55:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/N] Skip bun management when PAI is installed via Nix

The upstream installer's "make bun reachable for non-interactive
subprocess spawns" block (install.sh:146+) does two things — (a)
symlinks $HOME/.bun/bin/bun into a system-wide path (/usr/local/bin
or /opt/homebrew/bin), and (b) appends `export PATH="$HOME/.bun/bin:
$PATH"` to four shell rc files (.zshenv, .zprofile, .zshrc,
.bash_profile). Both target the upstream curl-installer flow where
bun is unmanaged.

Under any Nix install of PAI (NixOS, Nix-on-Ubuntu, Nix-on-macOS,
etc.), bun is supplied by the Nix store, the pai-nix wrapper injects
it into PATH explicitly, and there is no $HOME/.bun/bin/bun to
symlink. The upstream block then no-ops the symlink loop (no source
bun → loop body doesn't fire) but still pollutes shell rc files with
a stale export. Either way the work is wasted; the rc-file pollution
is unwelcome.

A second hunk in the same file (the post-install handoff at line 258+)
is also gated: under Nix the wrapper handles the launch, so the
interactive `exec zsh -i -c 'source ~/.zshrc && pai'` would block the
wrapper from continuing.

Fix — gate both blocks on a Nix-install marker. The companion
`export PAI_NIX_INSTALL=1` lives in default.nix's wrapper script.

Note: the initial version of this patch gated on `${NIX_STORE:-}`,
which is a build-time-only env var and therefore always empty at
install runtime. Patch 0005 corrects that by replacing every
NIX_STORE reference with the explicit PAI_NIX_INSTALL marker that
the wrapper exports. The intermediate state (after 0001 but before
0005) has the broken NIX_STORE gate; only the final post-0005 state
is correct.

Co-existence: patches 0004 and 0005 layer additional Nix-aware fixes
onto the same install.sh. Line ranges are non-overlapping with this
patch's hunks (this patch: lines 146..205 + 258..272).

---
--- a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/install.sh	2026-05-02 06:54:34.144383659 +0200
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/install.sh	2026-05-02 06:55:16.484549026 +0200
@@ -146,18 +146,10 @@
 fi

 # ─── Make bun reachable for non-interactive subprocess spawns ──────
-# Critical for Claude Code hooks (`#!/usr/bin/env bun` shebang). The bun
-# curl installer puts bun at ~/.bun/bin/bun and adds an export line to
-# .zshrc — but .zshrc is only sourced for interactive shells. Hooks
-# spawned by Claude Code inherit a non-interactive PATH where ~/.bun/bin
-# is missing, so every .hook.ts silently fails to launch (voice doesn't
-# fire, statusline can't run bun-based scripts, etc).
-#
-# Two-prong fix: (1) symlink to a system-wide location that's in every
-# default PATH so /usr/bin/env can find it without any shell config,
-# (2) add the export to .zshenv (which IS sourced for non-interactive zsh)
-# and .zprofile (login shells).
-if [ -x "$HOME/.bun/bin/bun" ]; then
+# On NixOS/Nix, bun is provided by the package manager and already on PATH
+# via the wrapper. Skip symlink creation and shell rc modifications — they
+# are unnecessary and would pollute the user's environment.
+if [ -z "${NIX_STORE:-}" ] && [ -x "$HOME/.bun/bin/bun" ]; then
   # System-wide symlink. Try writable target first; sudo only if needed.
   for target in /usr/local/bin /opt/homebrew/bin; do
     if [ -d "$target" ] && [ -w "$target" ] && [ ! -e "$target/bun" ]; then
@@ -175,12 +167,8 @@
   fi

   # Persist PATH to shell config files (idempotent).
-  # .zshenv is sourced for ALL zsh invocations including non-interactive subshells.
-  # .zprofile is sourced for login shells. .zshrc for interactive.
-  # .bash_profile for bash login. We cover all four to be robust.
   BUN_EXPORT='export PATH="$HOME/.bun/bin:$PATH"'
   for rc in "$HOME/.zshenv" "$HOME/.zprofile" "$HOME/.zshrc" "$HOME/.bash_profile"; do
-    # Create the file if it doesn't exist (touch is harmless).
     [ -f "$rc" ] || touch "$rc"
     if ! grep -q '\.bun/bin' "$rc" 2>/dev/null; then
       echo "" >> "$rc"
@@ -270,7 +258,11 @@
 #    nothing happened (the bug Daniel hit on server.baylander.lan).
 if [ "$INSTALL_EXIT" -eq 0 ]; then
   echo ""
-  if [ -r /dev/tty ]; then
+  # On NixOS/Nix, the wrapper handles post-install launch — skip the
+  # interactive shell handoff that would block the wrapper from continuing.
+  if [ -n "${NIX_STORE:-}" ]; then
+    success "Install complete."
+  elif [ -r /dev/tty ]; then
     info "Launching pai..."
     exec zsh -i -c 'source ~/.zshrc && pai' < /dev/tty
   else
